message.content:
Silene uniflora is a species of flowering plant in the family Caryophyllaceae.
The plant has a compact and cushion-like growth habit.
The leaves of Silene uniflora are lance-shaped and grayish-green in color.
The flowers are simple and delicate with five pink petals.
The petals are deeply notched at the tips, creating a fringed effect.
Silene uniflora is often found growing in meadows and on mountainsides in the northern hemisphere.
It is also commonly known as sea campion or one-flowered catchfly.
